Aedeagus almost straight, in its left lateral view (
Figs 37–38, 40–43
) dorsally shallowly excavated above the middle, the apical portion gradually conically attenuated towards apex, mostly ventrally shallowly emarginate towards blunt or nearly pointed apex; in its ventral view (
